<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-16T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="300" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">868.51/1283: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Great Britain (<persName type="to">Mellon</persName>)</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-16T18:00:00-05:00">November 16, 1932—6
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>283. Your 328, November 15, 5 p.m. The Department fails to understand
                                the reason for the failure of the British Government to <pb facs="0512" n="422" xml:id="pg_422"/> accede to the
                                representations you made on November 12. Immediately upon receipt of
                                the expected official reply telegraph a résumé thereof.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>